Package: surrogateTransportability
Type: Package
Title: Evaluating Surrogate Transportability via Local Geometric Analysis
Version: 0.4.0
Authors@R: person("Denis", "Agniel", email = "dagniel@rand.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Evaluates surrogate marker transportability from a single study by
    modeling hypothetical future studies as random probability measures within a
    local geometry around the observed study. The primary estimand is the
    correlation of treatment effects on the surrogate and outcome across future
    studies sampled uniformly (via hit-and-run MCMC) from a total-variation ball.
    Treatment effects are estimated by importance weighting (randomized trials)
    or cross-fitted augmented inverse probability weighting (observational
    studies), with influence-function-based inference. Traditional comparison
    methods (proportion of treatment effect, mediation, within-study correlation)
    are also provided.
